COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT by and among LOGAN WIND ENERGY LLC,a Delaware limited liability company, and PEETZ TABLE WIND, LLC,a Delaware limited liability company
and NORTHERN COLORADO WIND ENERGY CENTER, LLC,a Delaware limited liability company and NORTHERN COLORADO WIND ENERGY CENTER II, LLC,a Delaware limited liability company
COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT This COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is made and entered into as of August 25, 2020 (the “Effective Date”) by and among Logan Wind Energy LLC (“Logan Wind”), Peetz Table Wind, LLC (“Peetz Table Wind”), Northern Colorado Wind Energy Center, LLC (“Northern Colorado Wind I”), and Northern Colorado Wind Energy Center II, LLC (“Northern Colorado Wind II”), each of which is a Delaware limited liability company (each sometimes referred to herein individually as a “Party” or “Owner” and collectively as the “Parties” or “Owners”). RECITALS A. Logan Wind owns a wind power generation facility in Logan County, Colorado, with a Nameplate Capacity of approximately 200 MW (the “Logan Wind Project”). B. Peetz Table Wind will own a wind power generation facility in Logan County, Colorado, with a Nameplate Capacity of approximately 199.5 MW (the “Peetz Table Wind Project”). C. Northern Colorado Wind will own a wind power generation facility in Logan County, Colorado, with a Nameplate Capacity of approximately 151.8 MW (the “Northern Colorado Wind Project”). D. Northern Colorado Wind II will own a wind power generation facility in Logan County, Colorado, with a Nameplate Capacity of approximately 22.5 MW (the “Northern Colorado Wind II Project” and jointly with the Logan Wind Project, the Peetz Table Wind Project, and the Northern Colorado Wind Project, the “Projects,” or individually, “Project”). C. As represented in the Application for Authorization under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act and Request for Waivers and Expedited Action, filed with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission in Docket EC20-80, the Parties will be assigned joint ownership of certain transmission facilities within the Public Service Company of Colorado (“PSCO”) balancing authority area as depicted on Exhibit A (the “Common Facilities”) after such facilities are transferred by Peetz Logan Interconnect, LLC (“Peetz Logan Interconnect”). D. As a result of such assignment, the Owners will each have the following ownership share when this Agreement takes effect (as defined below, the “Proportionate Share”) in the Common Facilities: Logan Wind (34.86%), Peetz Table Wind (34.77%), Northern Colorado Wind I (26.46%), and Northern Colorado Wind II (3.92%). D. The Parties will use the Common Facilities to deliver the energy generated by the Projects to the physical point of interconnection with the PSCO grid, through separate generator interconnection agreements with PSCO to which Peetz Logan Interconnect (for Logan Wind and Peetz Table Wind) and Northern Colorado Interconnect, LLC (“Northern Colorado Interconnect”) (for Northern Colorado Wind I and Northern Colorado Wind II) are parties (the “Interconnection Agreements”), and the separate Shared Facilities Agreements among Peetz Logan Interconnect, Logan Wind and Peetz Table Wind, and among Northern Colorado Interconnect, LLC, Northern Colorado Wind I and Northern Colorado Wind (the “Shared Facilities Agreements”). E. The Parties are entering into this Agreement to describe their relative ownership interests in, and the Owners’ respective rights and obligations with respect to, the Common Facilities. This Agreement shall be the Owners’ expression of their intention to establish and impose mutually beneficial limitations, restrictions, covenants and conditions to provide for the proper and orderly ownership, operation and management of their respective Projects and the Common Facilities. NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt of which is hereby acknowledged, the Owners hereby agree as follows: CONSTRUCTION Rules of Interpretation. Unless otherwise expressly provided or unless required by the context in which any term appears: the singular includes the plural and the plural includes the singular; references to “Articles,” “Sections,” or “Exhibit” (if any) are references to articles, sections, or exhibit (if any) of this Agreement, as the same may be amended, modified, supplemented or replaced pursuant to the terms hereof from time to time; a reference to a particular Person includes its successors and permitted assigns, and in the case of any Governmental Authority, to any Person(s) succeeding to its functions and capacities; the words “herein,” “hereof” and “hereunder” and words of similar import refer to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular section or subsection of this Agreement; all accounting terms have the meanings assigned to them by generally acceptable accounting practices, as applied by the accounting entity to which they refer; references to this Agreement include the Exhibit hereto as the same may be amended, modified, supplemented or replaced from time to time; references to any contract or agreement will mean a reference to such contract or agreement as the same may be amended, modified, supplemented or replaced from time to time; the use of the word “including” in this Agreement to refer to specific examples will be construed to mean “including, without limitation” or “including but not limited to” and will not be construed to mean that the examples given are an exclusive list of the topics covered; relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “including and after,” “to” means “to but excluding”, “through” means “through and including”; any reference in this Agreement to a “day” or a number of “days” (without explicit reference to “Business Days”) means a reference to a calendar day or number of calendar days; whenever any action must be taken hereunder on, by, or within a time period ending on, a day that is not a Business Day, then such action may be taken on or by the next day that is a Business Day; references to applicable Laws mean such applicable Laws as the same may be amended, modified, supplemented or restated and be in effect from time to time, including rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; any representation or warranty contained herein as to the enforceability of a Contract (including this Agreement) is subject to the effect of any bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization, moratorium or other similar Law affecting the enforcement of creditors’ rights generally and to general equitable principles (regardless of whether such enforceability is considered in a proceeding in equity or at law); the word “or” shall be inclusive and shall have the meaning conveyed by “and/or,”; and all monetary figures are in United States dollars. The Parties collectively have prepared this Agreement, and none of the provisions hereof shall be construed against one Party on the ground that such Party is the author of this Agreement or any part hereof. Definitions. “Action” means any legal, administrative, arbitral, mediation or other alternative dispute resolution procedure or other action, proceeding, claim, suit, assessment, audit, inquiry or similar investigation before any court, arbitrator or other Authority, in all cases whether in law or in equity. “Affiliate” means, with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, is controlled by or is under common control with that Person. The term “control” (including, with correlative meaning, the terms “controlled by” and “under common control with”), as used with respect to any Person, means the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or ownership interests, by contract or otherwise. “Agreement” has the meaning set forth in the preamble. “Applicable Authorities” means FERC and the Colorado Public Utilities Commission. “Business Day” means any day other than Saturday, a Sunday, or any day on which banks located in Denver, Colorado, West Palm Beach, Florida, or the State of New York are authorized or required by Law to be closed. “Common Facilities Costs” means any expenses necessary, beneficial for, in connection with, or attributable to the use, operation, or maintenance of the Common Facilities, including, without limitation: All costs, fees, damages, reimbursements and expenses payable under any operation or maintenance agreement (including any mitigation or damages payments to underlying landowners); the operating costs associated with, and any capital upgrades and other expenses necessary for the operation of the Common Facilities, which operating costs may include, but shall not be limited to, road maintenance, weed abatement, equipment repairs, snow removal, and employee training; costs associated with scheduled and unscheduled maintenance, including any parts or supplies, heavy equipment, rentals, third party engineering, maintenance or consulting services required in order to maintain the Common Facilities in good working order; All costs, fees, damages and expenses to be paid in connection with decommissioning and removal of the Common Facilities and restoration of the underlying real property; All fees, rents or other, similar payments paid to any landowners who own the real estate upon which the Common Facilities are constructed; All costs and expenses to be paid in connection with repairing any damages to the Common Facilities; All consultant, expert and attorneys’ costs, expenses and fees incurred in connection with the above or with respect to any necessary or beneficial regulatory filings or proceedings concerning the Common Facilities. “Dispute” has the meaning set forth in Section 8.1. “Effective Date” has the meaning set forth in the preamble. “Encumbrance” means any claim, lien, pledge, mortgage, option, charge, easement, security interest, right-of-way, encumbrance, lease, interest, mineral reservations, covenant, conditional sales contract, title retention arrangement, adverse claim or restriction of any kind. “FERC” means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission and any successor entity. “Force Majeure Event” means any event that wholly or partly prevents or delays an Owner from timely performing all or a portion of its obligations under this Agreement or from complying with all or a portion of the conditions under this Agreement if such act or event (a) was not reasonably contemplated at the Effective Date, (b) was not within the reasonable control, directly or indirectly, of or the result of the negligence or fault of the affected Owner, or despite the exercise of reasonable diligence could not be prevented, avoided or removed by the affected Owner. A Force Majeure Event shall not include (i) lack of funds or finances or any obligation for the payment of money, (ii) unavailability of labor, equipment or materials unless resulting from an independent event that would separately constitute a Force Majeure Event, (iii) acts or omissions of a Governmental Authority regarding licenses and permits concerning the Common Facilities, or (iv) acts or omissions of contractors, subcontractors or any other Person providing labor or equipment to an Owner for the construction of its Project, unless resulting from an independent event that would separately constitute a Force Majeure Event. “Governmental Authority” means any court, tribunal, arbitrator, authority, agency, commission, official or other instrumentality of the United States or any state, county, city or other political subdivision or similar governing entity, and including any governmental, quasi-governmental or non-governmental body administering, regulating or having general oversight over natural gas, electricity, power or other markets. “Indemnified Owner” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1(a). “Indemnifying Owner” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1(a). “Information” means all information received pursuant to this Agreement or during the use or operation of the Common Facilities from an Owner or relating to an Owner or any of the Projects or businesses, other than any such information that is available to any Owner on a non-confidential basis prior to disclosure by the Owner to whom such Information relates, or is otherwise clearly non confidential in nature. “Laws” means any law, statute, rule, regulation, ordinance, standard, code, order, judgment, decision, writ, injunction, decree, certificate of need, award, Environmental Law or other governmental restriction, including any published and publicly available policy or procedure (or any guidelines or recommendations with respect to human health or safety or the use, handling, disposal or release of hazardous materials) issued or enforced by any Governmental Authority. “Lender” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1(c). “Lender Consent” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.26.2. “Lender’s Lien” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1(c). “Losses” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1(a). “Nameplate Capacity” means, with respect to a Project, the sum of the manufacturer’s maximum rated capacity of all wind turbines comprising such Project. “Owner(s)” has the meaning set forth in the preamble. “Party(ies)” has the meaning set forth in the preamble. “Person” means an individual, unincorporated association, and business entity of any type. “Project Controlled Assets” means, for each Owner, any of the assets solely comprising its respective Project (including each such Project’s transformer and meters), the corresponding Project lands and related Project agreements and contractual arrangements. For purposes of this term only, the Project Controlled Assets shall exclude the Common Facilities. “Proportionate Share” means, with respect to an Owner, the ratio (expressed as a percentage) (i) with a numerator equal to the maximum Nameplate Capacity of such Owner’s Project, and (ii) with a denominator equal to the maximum Nameplate Capacity of all of the Owners’ Projects in commercial operation at the time of the applicable calculation. The Owners’ respective Proportionate Shares at the time this Agreement takes effect are as stated in the Recitals. “Prudent Industry Practice” means the practices, methods and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the wind power industry in the United States in respect of the design, development, maintenance, financing, and operation of facilities of comparable type, size and complexity to the Common Facilities that, at a particular time, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known or that should reasonably have been known at the time a decision was made, would have been expected to accomplish the desired result in a manner consistent with applicable Laws, regulations, codes, standards, original equipment manufacturer’s recommendations, reliability, safety, environmental protection, economy and expedition. “Prudent Industry Practices” does not necessarily mean the best practice, method, or standard of care, skill, safety and diligence in all cases, but is instead intended to encompass a range of acceptable practices, methods and standards. “Transferring Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1. “Withdrawal Costs” has the meaning given in Section 11.3. OWNERSHIP AND USE OF COMMON FACILITIES Use of Common Facilities; Owner Responsibilities. Each Owner has the right to use its Proportionate Share of the Common Facilities to inject the output of its Project and transmit to the point of interconnection with PSCO. Priority of Use. In the event any Owner becomes aware of an equipment failure or an unanticipated event that requires the use of the Common Facilities to be curtailed to protect the Common Facilities, any Project, or human life, the Owner shall immediately notify each other Owner or its designated scheduling agent. The Owners agree to cooperate (either directly or through their respective scheduling agents) to curtail their Projects in response to such unanticipated event. During such curtailment each Owner shall curtail its respective Project on a proportional basis. To the extent any such curtailment or disconnection is directly caused by one Owner’s Project or the breach by an Owner of this Agreement, then, notwithstanding Section 2.1 above, such Owner’s Project shall be the first Project to be curtailed to the extent necessary or disconnected and the last Project to be permitted to fully use the Common Facilities following any such curtailment or disconnection. Station Service. Each Owner shall be responsible for paying for the retail station power service of its Project. OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF COMMON FACILITIES; EXPENSES Operation and Maintenance of the Common Facilities. Peetz Table Wind shall be responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Common Facilities. Peetz Table Wind will engage NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC (the “O&M Provider”') pursuant to an operation and maintenance agreement for the Common Facilities to be entered into by and between Peetz Table Wind and O&M Provider (the “O&M Agreement”). Each of the Owners agrees that the Common Facilities Costs, and any other costs and expenses of Peetz Table Wind related solely to the Common Facilities, shall be allocated amongst the Owners in accordance with their respective Proportionate Shares. Each of the Owners shall make its payment to Peetz Table Wind with respect to its share of any Common Facilities Costs, in a time and manner that will allow Peetz Table Wind to comply with its payment obligations under the O&M Agreement. Upon receipt of any information regarding Commons Facilities Costs, Peetz Table Wind shall immediately provide such information to the other Owners. Solely in connection with the services performed on the Common Facilities, Peetz Table Wind agrees to pursue all available remedies against the O&M Provider available to it under the O&M Agreement as may be commercially reasonable. The receipt of any payments for liability incurred by the O&M Provider under the O&M Agreement with respect to the Services performed on the Common Facilities shall be allocated amongst the Owners based on their respective Proportionate Shares, and Peetz Table Wind shall make payments to the other Owners for such allocations as soon as reasonably practical following its receipt of such liability payments from the O&M Provider. Successor Agreement. In the event that the Projects and the Common Facilities are no longer operated and maintained by a single entity for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the Owners and any entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Common Facilities Removal or Replacement of Owner Property. Each Owner shall have the express right, at any time and in its sole discretion, to remove and/or replace any part of its Project and all other property owned by such Owner, to the extent not jointly owned by the Owners. If removal or replacement of any of such property will materially affect in an adverse way the safety or operation of any of the Common Facilities, the Owner contemplating the removal or replacement shall consult with and obtain the consent of each of the other Owners before conducting the contemplated removal or replacement, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. OWNER APPROVALS Decision making regarding Common Facilities. The Owners agree that major decisions regarding construction, rebuilding, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement and removal of the Common Facilities, or any portion thereof, that have not otherwise been delegated to Peetz Table Wind or the O&M Provider in accordance with Section 3.1, must be unanimously decided by the Owners. For the avoidance of doubt, any decision (i) to remove from service permanently; (ii) to sell, transfer, assign or dispose of all or any part of the Common Facilities except in the ordinary course of business in instances where any disposed item is being repaired or replaced; (iii) that limits an Owner’s ability to generate or deliver energy from such Owner’s Project to the point of interconnection; or (iv) to incur or authorize the O&M Provider to incur any indebtedness related to the Common Facilities that the Owners would be obligated to repay pursuant to this Agreement (other than a Lender’s Lien against an individual Owner’s undivided interest incurred in accordance with Section 6.1(c) shall, in each case, require the unanimous approval of the Owners. COVENANTS Covenants of the Owners. The Owners hereby covenant as follows: Compliance with Law. Each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, promptly comply with all applicable Laws and with all covenants, conditions and restrictions in effect regulating the use of the Common Facilities or any facilities owned by such Owner thereon until this Agreement is terminated; provided, however, that such Owner shall have the right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings and in its own name the validity or applicability of any such applicable Law; and provided further that no such contest shall be permitted if it would expose the Common Facilities to a risk of loss by forfeiture or otherwise. Conduct of Activities. Each Owner shall (i) conduct its operations and activities of its Project in accordance with all applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices, applicable NERC reliability standards, and the Interconnection Agreements and Shared Facilities Agreements, and (ii) to the extent necessary to avoid a material adverse effect with respect to the condition or operation of the Common Facilities or an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto, keep its facilities in good condition and repair, in good and efficient working order and in a safe condition. No Owner shall conduct its operations or activities, or use or permit the use of the Common Facilities or any part thereof or its facilities in any manner that will cause physical damage to the Common Facilities or any part thereof, or cause an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto and each Owner shall be responsible for any such physical damage (but shall not incur any liability for any down-time resulting from any operations or activities conducted in accordance with applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices and otherwise in accordance with this Agreement). Subject to the terms of this Agreement, no Owner shall be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Common Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with, or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of, the Common Facilities by any other Owner. Confidentiality of Owner Information. Each Owner agrees to maintain the confidentiality of the Information, except that Information may be disclosed (i) to its Affiliates, managers, partners, directors, officers, employees, advisors, agents, consultants, lenders, and potential lenders, investors and purchasers to or of an Owner or any of its Affiliates (and their respective advisors, consultants and counsel); it being understood that the Persons to whom such disclosure is made will be informed of the confidential nature of such Information and required to keep such Information confidential pursuant to a confidentiality agreement or be under a duty to keep such Information confidential, (ii) to the extent required by any Applicable Authority or other Governmental Authority having jurisdiction over an Owner, a Project or the Common Facilities, (iii) to the extent required by applicable Laws or regulations or by any subpoena or similar legal process, (iv) in any legal action or proceeding relating to this Agreement or the Common Facilities, or (v) to the extent such Information (1) becomes publicly available other than as a result of a breach of this Section or (2) becomes available to any Owner on a non-confidential basis from a source other than the Owner (or a Person acting on behalf of such Owner) to whom such Information relates or a Person known to be bound by a contractual, legal, or fiduciary obligation to keep such information confidential. TRANSFER OF INTERESTS; LIENS Restrictions on Transfer. No Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its ownership interest or other rights or interests in or to the Common Facilities, or in, to or under this Agreement, without (i) assigning or transferring such Common Facilities and Agreement rights and interests together to the same assignee(s), such that the Common Facilities are not separated in ownership from the rights and interests under this Agreement, (ii) obtaining any necessary approval from FERC under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act, if applicable, and (iii) obtaining the prior written consent of all other Owners, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld by any such other Owners, except that such consent shall not be required for a sale, assignment or transfer by an Owner (a “Transferring Party”) in the following circumstances: the assignee or transferee is an entity with which the Transferring Party has consolidated or into which the Transferring Party has merged or which acquires by conveyance, transfer or lease all or substantially all of the assets of such Transferring Party and such purchaser, assignee, lessee or assignee shall have agreed in writing to assume all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement; or the assignee or transferee owns (or will own upon the transfer) an appropriate equivalent ownership interest in the Project(s) owned by the Transferring Party which produce electricity transmitted over the Common Facilities; or a transfer in the nature of a lien, security interest or collateral assignment of an Owner’s undivided interest in the Common Facilities or an Owner’s interest in this Agreement (each a “Lender’s Lien”) as security for a debt, equity or obligation to a third party (a “Lender”), or the foreclosure (or conveyance or assignment in lieu of foreclosure) of such Lender’s Lien; provided that, in the case of foreclosure of a Lender’s Lien, the requirements of Section 6.1(b) above are also met; provided, however, that no such assignment or a foreclosure on such assignment shall subordinate or otherwise adversely affect the rights of the other Owners in and to this Agreement or the Common Facilities covered hereby. The restrictions on transfer contained in this Section 6.1 shall not apply with respect to any merger, consolidation or transfer of equity ownership in an Owner itself, or in connection with the merger, consolidation, or transfer of assets, or equity interests in any entity, in either case owned by an owner, member, shareholder, or other Person owning an equity interest (directly or indirectly) in an Owner. Accommodation of Lenders. Each Owner shall provide such consents to collateral assignment, certifications, representations, estoppels, information or other documents, as may be reasonably requested by any other Owner in connection with the financing of such other Owner’s Project (generally, a “Lender Consent”), provided, however, that in providing a Lender Consent, no Owner shall have any obligation to (i) modify the terms of this Agreement, (ii) provide any consent or enter into any agreement that has a material adverse effect on any of such Owner’s rights, benefits, risks, or obligations under this Agreement, (iii) transfer or release any property or property interests of such Owner, (iv) release or subordinate (or cause the release or subordination of) any Encumbrance on any property of such Owner for the benefit of any other Owner or its lender, or (v) permit any Encumbrance to be placed on property of such Owner. The Owner requiring Lender Consent shall reimburse, or shall cause its lender to reimburse, the other Owners for the direct expenses (including the fees and expenses of counsel) incurred by them in the preparation, negotiation, execution and/or delivery of such Lender Consent and any documents requested by such Owner or its lender pursuant to this Section 6.2. DEFAULT AND REMEDIES Demand for Payment or Performance. Upon failure of an Owner to perform or cause to be performed any obligation to be performed by it, pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the other Owners may make demand upon said Owner for such performance. Performance Defaults. If an Owner materially fails to perform or cause to be performed any material obligation to be performed by it pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within thirty (30) calendar days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 7.1, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said thirty (30) calendar day period, then within a reasonable period following the date on which such Owner receives such demand provided cure is commenced within such thirty (30) calendar day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion, such failure shall, upon the expiration of the applicable grace period pursuant to this Section 7.2, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement; provided, however, that if such obligation is timely performed under protest pursuant to this Section 7.2, a default by such Owner with respect to performance of such obligation shall not be deemed to have occurred. Notwithstanding the foregoing provisions of this Section 7.2, in the case of any default of an Owner, to the extent that such Owner has provided written notice to the non-Defaulting Owner(s) of any lenders of such defaulting Owner to whom a Lender’s Lien has been granted, the non-Defaulting Owner(s) shall provide written notice of such default to any such lenders, and such lenders shall have the right (but not the obligation) for sixty (60) days after receipt of such notice to cure such default, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said sixty (60) calendar day period, then within a reasonable period not to exceed sixty (60) days following the date on which such lender receives such demand provided cure is commenced within such sixty (60) calendar day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion. Disputed Defaults. If an Owner disputes a default asserted against it by demand pursuant to Section 7.1, then such Owner may perform the obligation in dispute under protest and without prejudice to any rights or remedies that such Owner may have pursuant to any of this Agreement or at law or in equity. The Owner purportedly in default shall (a) deliver such protest in writing to each Owner making demand with respect thereto, (b) specify in such protest the reasons upon which the protest is based and (c) deliver a copy of such protest to each Owner. If such dispute is resolved in favor of the Owner upon whom demand was made, the Owner making demand upon such Owner shall reimburse to such Owner the amount of the costs and expenses incurred by such Owner in performing any obligation under rightful protest. Remedies. In addition to all other remedies permitted by law or under this Agreement (all of which shall be cumulative), following a default by an Owner, the non-defaulting Owners and their Lenders or other interest holders shall be entitled to perform the obligations of the defaulting Owner, and the defaulting Owner shall reimburse the performing Owners for any costs and expenses incurred in rendering such performance. Equitable Relief. The Owners agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for a breach by any Owner of its respective obligations under this Agreement, and that each Owner shall be entitled to seek injunctive and other equitable relief, including specific performance, against any other Owner to prevent or eliminate any default. Separate Defaults. Each act or omission to act that constitutes a default under this Agreement shall be treated as a separate default under this Article 7. DISPUTE RESOLUTION Dispute Resolution. In the event of a dispute, action, suit or proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement or transactions contemplated by this Agreement, including any question regarding its existence, validity, interpretation, or termination (each a “Dispute”) between the Parties, the Parties will use all reasonable efforts to reach a satisfactory solution by referring the Dispute to executive representatives of each of the Parties. Upon a Party’s written notification to the other Party of a Dispute, which notification must include a written explanation of the Dispute and the material particulars of the notifying Party’s position as to the dispute, each Party shall nominate one (1) executive representative with the authority to bind such Party. The nominated representatives shall meet not later than ten (10) Business Days thereafter to attempt in good faith to resolve the Dispute. Submission to Jurisdiction. The Parties hereby irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the federal court in the Southern District of New York for purposes of any Action arising out of this Agreement or any transaction contemplated hereby and each Party hereby consents to the jurisdiction of such court (and of the appropriate appellate courts therefrom) in any such Action, and irrevocably waives, to the fullest extent permitted by Law, any objection that it may now or hereafter have to the laying of the venue of any such Action in any such court or that any such Action that is brought in any such court has been brought in an inconvenient forum. During the period a legal dispute filed in accordance with this Section 8.2 is pending before a court, all Actions with respect to such legal dispute or any other legal dispute, including any counterclaim, cross-claim or interpleader, will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of such court. Each Party hereby waives, and will not assert as a defense in any legal dispute, that (i) such Party is not subject thereto, (ii) such Action may not be brought or is not maintainable in such court, (iii) such Party’s property is exempt or immune from execution, (iv) such Action is brought in an inconvenient forum, or (v) the venue of such Action is improper. A final judgment in any Action described in this Section 8.2 following the expiration of any period permitted for appeal and subject to any stay during appeal will be conclusive and may be enforced in other jurisdictions by suit on the judgment or in any other manner provided by applicable Laws. Service of Process. Each of the Parties hereby consents to process being served by the other Party to this Agreement in any Action of the nature specified in Section 8.2 by mailing of a copy thereof in accordance with the provisions of Section 10.1 of this Agreement. Waiver Of Jury Trial; Remedies. Each of the Parties hereto waives any right it may have to trial by jury in respect of any claim based on, arising out of, under or in connection with this Agreement or any course of conduct, course of dealing, verbal or written statement or action of any Party hereto in connection with the transactions contemplated hereby. Continuation of Obligations. Pending final resolution of any dispute, the Parties shall continue to fulfill their respective obligations hereunder. Governing Law. This Agreement shall be construed, interpreted and the rights of the Parties determined in accordance with the Laws of the State of New York without giving effect to any conflict or choice of law provision that would result in the application of another state’s Law. INDEMNITY; LIMITATION ON DAMAGES Indemnity. General Indemnity. Each Owner (an “Indemnifying Owner”) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Owners (an “Indemnified Owner”) from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, claims, judgments, liens, penalties, costs and expenses (including, without limitation, reasonable attorneys’ fees), which may be imposed upon or incurred by such Indemnified Owner or asserted against such Indemnified Owner by any third Person (i) in connection with any material breach of this Agreement by such Indemnifying Owner and any grossly negligent or willful misconduct by such Indemnifying Owner and (ii) subject to the terms of this Agreement, with respect to the Indemnifying Owner’s Project Controlled Assets (collectively, “Losses”). Payment of Losses. The Indemnifying Owner shall pay all undisputed costs, expenses and/or revenue losses under this Section 9.1 within five (5) Business Days after the receipt of an invoice for the same. Except with respect to indemnification for amounts that are taxable upon receipt (including lost revenues), any amounts paid as indemnification under this Section 9.1 shall be (i) increased to take account of any tax cost incurred (including a gross-up to take account of the tax cost of such increase) by the Indemnified Owner arising from the receipt of payments pursuant to Section 9.1(a) and (ii) reduced to take account of any tax benefit realized by the Indemnified Owner arising from the incurrence of the Losses with respect to which payments are made pursuant to Section 9.1(a). In computing the amount of any such tax cost or tax benefit, the actual combined federal and state tax rate applicable to the Indemnified Owner shall be used. The amount of any such tax benefit or tax cost that is deferred or will be realized over time (including, without limitation, depreciation or amortization deductions) shall be the net present value of the future benefits or costs, as applicable, using a discount rate equal to the mid-term applicable federal rate in effect on the day on which the related amounts are paid as indemnification under this Section 9.1. Limitation on Damages. Except as expressly provided in this Agreement, no Party or its Affiliates, or their respective representatives will be liable for special, punitive, exemplary, or consequential damages of any other Party or of such Party’s Affiliates or its or its Affiliates’ Representatives, whether based on contract, tort, strict liability, other Law or otherwise and whether or not arising from the other Party’s or its Affiliates’, or an of their respective Representatives’ sole, joint or concurrent negligence, strict liability or other fault; provided that the foregoing will not apply to third-party claims for which any Party is obligated to indemnify another Party hereunder. NOTICES Form of Notices. All notices or other communications required or permitted by this Agreement shall be in writing. Except to the extent otherwise expressly provided in Section 6.1b, the duties, obligations and liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement are intended to be several and not joint or collective, and no Owner shall be jointly or severally liable for the acts, omissions or obligations of any other Owner. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement. Term and Termination. The term of this Agreement shall commence as of the Effective Date, or at such later time approved by FERC, and, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, shall terminate upon the mutual agreement of all the Owners. Abandonment or Decommissioning of a Project. If an Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Project, and the undivided interests of such Owner are not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the surrendering Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the surrendering Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owners of its intent to abandon its Project, be responsible for its cost allocation (as determined in accordance with the such Owner’s Proportionate Share as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Common Facilities, as applicable (collectively, the “Withdrawal Costs”). The Owners shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows: The Owners shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the surrendering Owner within forty-five (45) days of receiving notice of Owner’s intent to abandon its Project. The surrendering Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained in a reserve account and used for removal of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the shared premises when same becomes necessary. Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder and without limiting any other remedies available to the other Owners hereunder or at law or equity, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its undivided interests hereunder to the other Owners and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Common Facilities. Distribution on Termination of This Agreement. In the event that the Owners decide to decommission all of the Projects and to proceed with the removal of the Common Facilities, the Owners shall take account of all the Owners’ joint assets covered by this Agreement, including the Common Facilities, and joint liabilities pursuant to this Agreement and shall proceed with the liquidation thereof. The assets covered by this Agreement shall be liquidated as promptly as is consistent with obtaining a reasonable value therefor, and the proceeds therefrom, together with any assets distributed in-kind, shall be applied and distributed as follows: To the payment of debts and liabilities of the Owners to third parties in connection with the Common Facilities, which are then due and the expenses of liquidation. To the setting up of any reserves that the Owners deem necessary for any contingent or unforeseen liabilities or obligations or debts not yet payable by the Owners in connection with the Common Facilities, including any reserves to pay costs associated with the decommissioning and removal of the Common Facilities. To the distribution to Owners based on their respective Proportionate Shares. Uncontrollable Forces. No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. Any Owner rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each of the Owners and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability and thereafter resume performance with all reasonable dispatch. Estoppel Certificates. Upon the request of an Owner, any other Owner, upon not less than ten (10) Business Days’ notice, shall, if true, provide a certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or Lender with respect to such Owner’s portion of the Common Facilities, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner in such certificate. Partition Waiver. The Owners agree that the Common Facilities are not suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under applicable Law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Common Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Common Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 6 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. Amendments. This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties; provided however, that any Owner requesting an amendment or modification pursuant to this Section 11.8 that requires, or results in, a filing with, or notification of, any Applicable Authority shall as promptly as practicable notify the other Owners and shall cooperate with the other Owners as reasonably necessary, in each case so that the other Owners will be able to comply with any applicable regulations of the Applicable Authorities, including the filing of certificates of concurrence and tariff records. For purposes of clarification, transfers or assignments otherwise permitted hereunder shall not be deemed amendments to this Agreement. Further Assurances. The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably requested by the Parties to implement this Agreement so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. Condemnation. If all or part of the Common Facilities is proposed to be taken as the result of any action or proceeding in eminent domain, or is proposed to be transferred in lieu of condemnation to any Governmental Authority entitled to exercise the power of eminent domain (collectively, a “Taking”), any Owner receiving notice shall provide the other Owners with reasonable advance notice of any impending proceeding or meeting related to such Taking and shall not in the absence of approval of the Owners in accordance with Section 4.1, settle with the Governmental Authority doing the Taking or agree on compensation for such Taking. This Agreement shall terminate as to any portion of the Common Facilities so condemned or taken. Any award or other compensation payable as a consequence of such Taking shall be paid to the Owners according to their respective Proportionate Shares. Partial Invalidity. Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall this Agreement continue for a term that is longer than the longest periods permitted by applicable Law. No Third Party Beneficiaries. Except with respect to the rights of Indemnified Owners as set forth herein, and (for any Lender that has provided financing to an Owner in reliance on such provisions) the provisions of Section 6, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns, and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not an Owner.
